Description: SearchLawrence.com is a real estate search engine that provides detailed information on properties in Lawrence, Kansas.
Full Description: [SearchLawrence.com](http://www.searchlawrence.com/) provides detailed real estate information focused on the Lawrence, KS real estate market.  Visitors can [search for homes](http://www.searchlawrence.com/Homes_For_Sale_In_Lawrence_KS_Map_Search.php), get [market statistics](http://www.searchlawrence.com/Lawrence_Kansas_Real_Estate_Trends.php), view upcoming [open houses](http://www.searchlawrence.com/Lawrence_KS_Open_Homes.php) in the area, [calculate mortgage payments](http://www.searchlawrence.com/Lawrence_Kansas_Mortgage_Calculators.php) and find [videos](http://www.searchlawrence.com/Real_Estate_Video_Library.php), tools and advice about buying a home in Lawrence, KS. Although the website is owned and operated by Lawrence, Kansas REALTOR, Tanya Kulaga of Realty Executives, Hedges Real Estate, and features her clients homes on the front page of the website, the site provides access to residential listing data from all major area brokers collected from three Multiple Listing Services (Topeka MLS, Lawrence MLS and Heartland MLS). The website has a strict no advertising policy and is ad free.  SearchLawrence.com also attempts to present data on it's [property search](http://www.searchlawrence.com/Homes_For_Sale_In_Lawrence_KS_Map_Search.php), [map search](http://www.searchlawrence.com/Homes_For_Sale_In_Lawrence_KS_Map_Search.php) and real estate [resource pages](http://www.searchlawrence.com/Lawrence_Kansas_Home_Buyers_Resources.php) in a fair and unbiased way to site visitors.  The sites primary goal is to help buyers research the Lawrence real estate market by offering access to  data and resources so they can draw their own conclusions.
Industry Groups: Advertising, Internet Services, Real Estate, Sales and Marketing

Full Description: StrategyHack teaches marketers to be leaders in problem-solving and strategy development through a live-action, hands-on workshop with real startups. The goal is to create a strategy for each startup that will accelerate growth and profitability by the end of the day. Dealing with real companies in real scenarios raises the stakes and provides a new level of motivation, accountability, and responsibility. StrategyHack's time-limited workshops teach employees to gain a quick understanding of an unfamiliar target market, as well as deliver actionable strategies to achieve specific outcomes. Their method is backed up by experience and measurable data. They've spent the past two years hosting these marketing accelerators, and they've successfully matched more than 60 startups with 180 strategists. Agencies and brands from Boston to Atlanta have sent marketers to participate, and startups have come from as far away as San Francisco and Tel Aviv.

Description: Matching College Students and Startups
Full Description: HireStarts is a social network designed by students, for students. We are an online community for students to showcase themselves to potential employers, and access opportunities not found anywhere else. HireStarts seeks to modernize the hiring process for OUR generation. Our mission is for students to be able to find exciting internships and careers, with fast-growth companies, while still focusing on school.  Our team knows the issues with the current hiring process, because we were going through the same struggle as college seniors in Fall of 2011. We have built a resource both students and companies have taken advantage of, bringing the brightest candidates to the top companies with just a click of the mouse. HireStarts is showcasing students with their unique skills and abilities to help create the strongest workforce available.  Concept in October of 2011, and our first beta launched in April 2012, we have spent countless hours perfecting our network. Our number one priority is to make sure everything we create benefits our consumers. We are not developing our network from the executive floor; instead we are on your campus, in your classrooms, and at your career fairs to make sure we can bring the necessary tools to your hands, and get you hired. School should be the biggest priority to a college student, and we strive to make sure you are able to find a job you can be passionate about, without spending an unnecessary amount of time doing so.  Saving money on recruiting, career fairs, sorting resumes, and contacting candidates allows our companies to focus on more important goals. Never worry about hiring under qualified or undesirable employees ever again. We want our companies to be able to meet our qualified candidates before contacting them, and ensure that they hire the right candidate that will fit culture and thrive in their specific work environment.

A universe of online communities
Full Description: Cubits.org is a collection of communities, called cubits. Each cubit is a self-contained mini-website devoted to the specific interests of that community. Cubits.org was created by Dave Whitinger, the founder of LinuxToday.com and DavesGarden.com. You have probably visited websites devoted to specific subjects. They usually contain forums, a member list, informational databases, file uploads, and the like. Each of these websites were painstakingly created by the website's owner, who devoted hundreds of hours to putting it all together. There are countless people who have a great interest in some particular subject, and would love to make a community website about it, but they don't have the expertise to create it. Thus, Cubits.org was created to let anybody start their own feature-rich community website. With no technical knowledge required, a person can come to Cubits.org and within minutes have their own community website ready for their members. In the first 6 weeks after launch, there were already over 500 communities created with more than 100,000 posts in the various forums.

Description: Biodegradable Cleaning Additives
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Sunsonix makes the most efficient cleaning solutions (consumable chemicals) to maximize the removal of trace metal contaminants from very delicate devices/substrates during manufacturing processes. Sunsonix was formed by a team of experts, who together have over 100 years of experience in the semiconductor, device surface engineering and chemical industries (e.g., Siemens, Air Products). The combined talent of this team has pushed the limits of substrate cleaning chemistries and manufacturing processes to improve device performance while reducing waste, and cost. Sunsonix specializes in surface engineering, focusing on micro contamination control in a wide variety of industrial processes of Photovoltaics, semiconductor and high technology markets. The cleaner the device, the better the performance (higher energy efficiency for Photovoltaics, faster processing speed with semiconductors). The beauty of the Sunsonix approach is the non-toxic, biodegradable and biocompatible (e.g. – Green!) nature of the chemistries. Sunsonix cleaning technology has the unparalleled ability to work in concert with existing process sequences, both acidic and alkaline, to aid the removal of surface bound transition metals without damage to the underlying device, resulting in device performance improvements and process/chemical consumption optimization.
Industry Groups: Energy, Hardware, Manufacturing, Natural Resources, Science and Engineering, Sustainability
